      <div class="msgContentFrame">Yeah, it would definitely be great, being able to Spectate the high level Guild v Guild &amp; Tournament matches. It's the same thing I do with Starcraft 2 and it's commentaries. <br /> <br />I also hope the World PvP gets its own Spectator Mode as well, because it could provide for some interesting uses for people like the machinma community. Being able to record epic battles, from a camera perspective would be interesting indeed. However there will need to be some limitations such as: <br /><ul> 
<li>Having the camera lock onto only players, from your own server; to prevent spying on enemy player's movements.</li> 
<li>No in-game chat allowed, for the same reason as above.</li> 
<li>Not being able to join, right after exiting Spectator mode (some kind of cooldown).</li> 
</ul> <br /> <br />I think a Spectator system like this could work well in World PvP.</div>
